name: mirdhyn-iis

summary: Puppet module for configuring IIS. It can configure application pools, sites, applications, virtual directories, settings and custom error pages.

properties.name: error_pages
properties.doc:
Array of hashes containing list of error pages.
      Each hash must contain following keys: statusCode, path and responseMode.
      Optional keys are subStatusCode,:prefixLanguageFilePath.
      Possible values for responseMode are 'File', 'ExecuteURL' and 'Redirect'.
      Example:
        iis_errorpages {'Default Web Site/test':
          error_pages => [{statusCode => 404, prefixLanguageFilePath => '/lang/', path => '/errors/404.html', responseMode => 'ExecuteURL'},
                          {statusCode => 500, subStatusCode => 100, path => 'C:mywebsiterr@.100.html', responseMode => 'File'}]
        }

parameters.name: name
parameters.doc: Site, app, vdir or directory name

properties.doc: Physical path of the site

properties.name: id
properties.doc: Number assigned to a site when it is created. Default Web Site has an id of 1. Other sites are assigned a random id by IIS when they are created

properties.name: serverautostart
properties.doc: Whether the site should be started automatically when the IIS management service is started

properties.name: limits_maxbandwidth
properties.doc: Limits: Maximum network bandwidth in bytes per second to be consumed by the site

properties.name: limits_maxconnections
properties.doc: Limits: Maximum number of simultaneous client connections for a site

properties.name: limits_connectiontimeout
properties.doc: Limits: The amount of time in seconds that IIS waits before disconnecting a connection that has become inactive

properties.name: logfile_logextfileflags
properties.doc: Logging: The categories of information that are logged

properties.name: logfile_directory
properties.doc: Logging: Directory that log files and supporting logging files are saved to

properties.name: logfile_period
properties.doc: Logging:

properties.name: logfile_truncatesize
properties.doc: Logging: Maximum size in bytes for the log file. When reached, a new log file will be created. Only applies when logfile_period is set to MaxSize.  Minimum value for this property is 1,048,576

properties.name: logfile_localtimerollover
properties.doc: Logging: Whether when a new log file is created based on time, this is done based on UTC or local time.  false indicates UTC, true indicates local time

properties.name: logfile_enabled
properties.doc: Logging: Whether logging is enabled

properties.name: tracefailedrequestslogging_customactionsenabled
properties.doc: Trace failed requests logging: Whether custom actions are enabled
